ge.cfm?u=638&c=2563|title=Wreck of the Ethel|website=www.samemory.sa.gov.au|access-date=2018-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026064800/http://www.samemory.sa.gov.au/site/page.cfm?u=638&c=2563|archive-date=26 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|{{coord|35.298698 |S|136.891945|E|format=dms|name=Ethel}} \n|-\n|''Fanny''\n|22 June 1838\n|A [[schooner]] that was blown ashore near [[Cape Jaffa]], [[Kingston District Council]].\n|\n|-\n|{{SS|Ferret}}\n|14 November 1920\n|A [[steamship]] that was fraudulently taken from its home in Scotland, and arrived in Victoria six months later. The conspirators were caught and charged, but the ship remained in Australia, eventually running aground off [[Cape Spencer (South Australia)|Cape Spencer]] in a storm.\n|\n|-\n|[[Frances (1839)|''Frances'']]\n|29 August 1840\n|A [[cutter (boat)|cutter]] that was wrecked in the [[Neptune Island]]s.\n|{{coord|35|33|00|S|136|12|00|E|name=Frances}}.\n|-\n|''Gloridia V''\n|12 March 1977\n|A cray-fishing boat that was wrecked in the [[Neptune Island|North Neptune Islands]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Geltwood]]''\n|14 June 1876\n|A [[barque]] that struck a reef near the town of [[Southend, South Australia|Southend]].\n|{{coord|37|37|36|S|140|10|51|E|name=Geltwood}}\n|-\n|''[[Grecian (barque)]]''\n|13 October 1850\n|A [[barque]] that sank in a gale off [[Port Adelaide]], one man drowned.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article38447955 |title=Loss of the Barque \"Grecian\". |newspaper=[[South Australian Register]] |location=Adelaide |date=15 October 1850 |accessdate=2 February 2016 |page=2 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|[[Hougomont (barque)|''Hougomont'']]\n|8 January 1933\n|A [[barque]] that was scuttled as a breakwater in [[Stenhouse Bay, South Australia|Stenhouse Bay]].\n|\n|-\n|[[Investigator (steamship)|''Investigator'']]\n|24 April 1917\n|A [[steamship]] that sank in rough weather southwest of [[Wardang Island]].<ref name=SAwrecks/>\n|\n|-\n|''[[Koenig