orge III'']]\n|12 March 1835\n|A [[convict ship]] that sank in the [[D'Entrecasteaux Channel]].\n|{{coord|43.51|S|146.98|E|name=George III (ship)}}\n|-\n|{{ship||Hebe|1803 ship|2}}\n|15 June 1808\n|A ship that struck a reef off [[George Town, Tasmania|George Town]].\n|{{coord|41|03|42.92|S|146|45|18.90|E|name=Hebe (ship)}}\n|-\n|[[MV Iron Baron (1985)|MV ''Iron Baron'']]\n|10 July 1995\n|A [[bulk carrier]] that ran aground on a reef off [[George Town, Tasmania|George Town]], causing an oil spill. It was refloated and scuttled off [[Flinders Island]].\n|{{Coord|-39.22|149.13|name=MV Iron Baron (1985)}}\n|-\n|[[TSS Kanowna|TSS ''Kanowna'']]\n|18 February 1929\n|One of Tasmania's largest shipwrecks, found in 2005 in [[Bass Strait]].\n|\n|-\n|[[MV Lake Illawarra|MV ''Lake Illawarra'']]\n|5 January 1975\n|Bulk carrier wrecked in the [[River Derwent (Tasmania)|River Derwent]], with 12 lives lost.\n|{{coord|42|51|52|S|147|20|45|E|name=MV Lake Illawarra}}\n|-\n|''[[Nella Dan]]''\n|24 December 1987\n|An [[icebreaker]] that ran aground off [[Macquarie Island]], and was subsequently scuttled.\n|\n|-\n|[[Netherby (ship)|''Netherby'']]\n|23 July 1866\n|A [[full-rigged ship]] that ran aground off [[King Island (Tasmania)|King Island]].\n|\n|-\n|[[Neva (1813 ship)|''Neva'']]\n|13 May 1835\n|A [[convict ship]] that sank off [[King Island (Tasmania)|King Island]], with about 225 lives lost.\n|\n|-\n|''[[Phatisalam]]''\n|9 July 1821\n|A ship that ran aground on [[Hunter Island (Tasmania)|Hunter Island]].\n|\n|-\n|[[Sydney Cove (1796 ship)|''Sydney Cove'']]\n|9 February 1797\n|Sank at [[Preservation Island]] with no loss of life.\n|{{Coord|40.49|S|148.07|E|name=Sydney Cove (ship)}}\n|}\n\n==Victoria==\n{{see also|Shipwreck Coast}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" | style = \"width:100%\"\n! style=\"width:10%\" | Ship\n! style=\"width:10%\" | Sunk date\n! style=\"width:70%\" | Notes\n! style=\"width:10%\" | Coordinates\n|-\n|{{SS|Alert}}\n|28 December 1893\n|A [[steamship]] that sank o