 [[barque]] that went down in a storm off [[Mandurah]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Koolama]]''\n|3 March 1942\n|A [[merchant vessel]] that was bombed by Japanese aircraft and later capsized at [[Wyndham, Western Australia|Wyndham]]. The wreck was towed further out to sea in 1948.\n|\n|-\n|[[MV Korean Star (1984)|MV ''Korean Star'']]\n|20 May 1988\n|A Panamanian [[bulk carrier]] that was lost off Cape Cuvier.\n|\n|-\n|[[German auxiliary cruiser Kormoran|''Kormoran'']]\n|19 November 1941\n|German [[merchant raider]] [[scuttling|scuttled]] after being damaged in battle by {{HMAS|Sydney|1934|6}}.\n|{{Coord|26|05|46|S|111|04|33|E|name=German auxiliary cruiser Kormoran}}\n|-\n|[[SS Kwinana|''S.S. Kwinana'']]\n|29 May 1922\n|A [[steamship]] wrecked in a storm off [[City of Kwinana|Kwinana]].\n|\n|-\n|[[Lady Elizabeth (1869)|''Lady Elizabeth'']]\n|30 June 1878\n|A [[barque]] that struck a reef off [[Rottnest Island]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Lady Lyttleton]]''\n|17 July 1867\n|A [[barque]] that sank in Emu Point Channel near [[Albany, Western Australia|Albany]]\n|{{coord|-34.997717|117.95031|name=Lady Lyttleton}}\n|-\n|[[RMS Orizaba|RMS ''Orizaba'']]\n|February 17, 1905\n|A [[Royal Mail Ship]] that ran aground off [[Rockingham, Western Australia|Rockingham]].\n|{{coord|-32.278613|115.624866|name=RMS Orizaba}}\n|-\n|{{SS|Pericles}}\n|31 March 1910\n|An [[ocean liner]] that struck a rock and sank 6 miles south of [[Cape Leeuwin]].\n|{{coord|-34.42217|115.13733|name=SS Pericles}}\n|-\n|{{HMAS|Perth|D 38|6}}\n|24 November 2001\n|A [[Perth-class destroyer|''Perth''-class]] [[guided missile destroyer]] scuttled as a [[dive wreck]] off [[Albany, Western Australia|Albany]].\n|{{Coord|-35.085|117.96|name=HMAS Perth (D 38)}}\n|-\n|''Redemptora''\n|C. 1898\n|A wooden [[Clipper]] abandoned or sunk off [[Cockburn, Western Australia|Cockburn]].\n|<ref>https://www.researchgate.net/publication/327622688_The_Clipper_Ship_Redemptora_1851-1898_A_Study_in_Archaeology_History_and_Heritage_Management</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Sanko Harvest]]''\n|14 February 1991\n|A [[bulk carrier]] that struck a reef off [[Esperance, Western Australia|Esperance]].\n|{{coord|34|7.4|S|122|5.1|E|name=Sanko Harvest}}\n|-\n|{{HMAS|Swan|DE 50|6}}\n|14 December 1997\n|A [[River-class destroyer escort|River-class]] [[destroyer escort]] that was sunk as a dive wreck off [[Dunsborough, Western Australia|Dunsborough]].\n|{{coord|33|33|02|S|115|06|02|E|name=HMAS Swan (DE 50)}}\n|-\n|{{HMAS|Sydney|1934|6}}\n|19 November 1941\n|[[Leander-class cruiser (1931)|Leander class cruiser]] sunk in battle by the German [[merchant raider]] [[German auxiliary cruiser Kormoran|''Kormoran'']].\n|{{Coord|26|14|31|S|111|12|48|E|name=HMAS Sydney (1934)}}\n|-\n|{{HMAS|Torrens|DE 53|6}}\n|14 June 1999\n|A [[River-class destroyer escort|River-class]] [[destroyer escort]] that was sunk as a target.\n|\n|-\n|''[[Tryall]]''\n|25 May 1622\n|[[Honourable East India Company]] ship.\n|\n|-\n|{{HMS|Undine|1881|6}}\n|25 March 1890\n|A [[gunboat]] that was wrecked in the [[King George Sound]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Vergulde Draeck]]''\n|28 April 1656\n|Dutch VOC merchant sailing ship.\n|{{coord|31|13.36|S|115|21.48|E|name=Vergulde Draeck}}\n|-\n|{{HMAS|Wallaroo}}\n|11 June 1943\n|A [[Bathurst-class corvette|''Bathurst''-class]] [[corvette]] that collided with the ''Henry Gilbert Costin'' off [[Fremantle]].\n|{{coord|31|54|24|S|114|37|31|E|name=HMAS Wallaroo}}\n|-\n|[[Wave (brig)|''Wave'']]\n|5 July 1848\n|A [[brig]] sunk off Cheynes Beach near [[Cape Riche]]\n|{{coord|34.5945|S|118.75165|E|name=Wave}}\n|-\n|{{SS|Xantho}}\n|1872\n|A [[steamship]] that sank off [[Gregory, Western Australia|Gregory]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Zeewijk]]''\n|9 June 1727\n|Dutch VOC merchant sailing ship.\n|{{coord|28|54|30|S|113|49|0|E|name=Zeewijk}}\n|-\n|''[[Zuytdorp]]''\n|1712\n|Dutch VOC merchant sailing ship.\n|{{coord|27|11|10|S|113|56|13|E|name=Zuytdorp}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Australian National Shipwreck Database]]\n* [[List of unidentified shipwrecks in Australian waters]]\n* [