ll]].\n|{{coord|34|7|48|S|136|21|36|E|name=Lady Kinnaird (1877)}}\n|-\n|''[[Loch Sloy]]''\n|24 April 1899\n|A [[barque]] that was wrecked in the Brothers Rocks, off [[Kangaroo Island]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Loch Vennachar]]''\n|September 1905\n|A [[clipper]] that sank off [[Kangaroo Island]] with the loss of 27 lives.\n|{{coord|35|53|05|S|136|32|00|E|name=Loch Vennachar}}\n|-\n|[[Macintyre (schooner)|''Macintyre'']]\n|1 April 1927\n|A [[schooner]] that was wrecked on a reef off [[Wardang Island]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Maria (brigantine)|Maria]]''\n|28 June 1840\n|A [[brigantine]] that was wrecked off [[Cape Jaffa]], South Australia\n|\n|-\n|''Marion''\n|11 July 1862\n|A screw steamer wrecked off [[Cable Hut Bay]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/shipwreck/public/wreck/wreck.do?key=5568|title=SHIPWRECKS - View|website=www.environment.gov.au|access-date=2018-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026064651/http://www.environment.gov.au/shipwreck/public/wreck/wreck.do?key=5568|archive-date=26 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|''[[No 5 dumb hopper barge]]''\n|April 1984\n|A [[hopper barge]] that was scuttled in [[Gulf St Vincent]].\n|{{coord|34|31|S|138|03|E|name=No 5 dumb hopper barge}}\n|-\n|''[[Notre Dame d'Avor]]''\n|20 March 1920\n|A [[barque]] that ran aground on [[Wardang Island]]. The wreck was gutted by an accidental fire the following May.<ref name=SAwrecks/>\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Postboy (ship)|Postboy]]''\n|1905\n|A [[schooner]] that was wrecked at [[Arno Bay, South Australia|Arno Bay]].\n|{{coord|33|55|12|S|136|34|12|E|name=Postboy}}\n|-\n|''Saint Michele''\n|30 March 1965\n|A fishing boat that was wrecked on [[Neptune Island|South Neptune Islands]].\n|\n|-\n|''[[Santiago (1856 ship)|Santiago]]''\n|19 August 1945\n|A 3 masted [[barque]] abandoned in the Garden Island Ships' Graveyard near [[Port Adelaide]].\n|{{coord|34|48|36|S|138|32|24|E|name=Santiago}}\n|-\n|''[[Songvaar]]''\n|14 April 1912\n|A Norwegian [[cargo ship]] that sank near 